text:
Q: How to get the active monitor count in Delphi VCL? A: <p>I found that you can use the <a href="https://docwiki.embarcadero.com/Libraries/Florence/en/Vcl.Forms.TScreen.MonitorCount" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><code>Screen.MonitorCount</code></a> function from the <a href="https://docwiki.embarcadero.com/Libraries/Florence/en/Vcl.Forms" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><code>Vcl.Forms</code></a> unit.</p>
<p>You can see them like this:</p>
<pre><code>procedure TForm1.Button1Click(Sender: TObject);
begin
  ShowMessage('Monitor count: ' + Screen.MonitorCount.ToString);
end;
</code></pre>
<p>And that would show the amount of monitors you have in a <code>ShowMessage</code> dialog.</p>
